What you need to know:  This year the event which comes two weeks after the season-opener, the Sigona Bowl won by Royal Nairobi’s Jay Sandhu, has attracted a field of 101In the absence of the of the Magical Kenya Open bound players, Nandi Bears Golf Club’s Nelson Koech, Peter Rimui of Nanyuki, Chris Andrea of Ruiru, Ebill Omollo and Isaac Makokha of Vet Lab will be some of the players to watch this weekendMeanwhile down at the Coast, a strong field of 250 players are all set to tackle the par 71 Nyali Golf and Country Club course in Mombaa’s mainland north during the Chairman’s Prize being hosted by outgoing chairman Taib Bajaber